data.title: Top 15 PSP Games
data.meta_description: A list of the 15 best games for the PlayStation Portable
data.text:
Kratos is still haunted by the visions of his mortal past and decides to explore his origins. In Atlantis, he finds his mother Callisto, who claims that his brother Deimos is still alive.

Follows a young man, named Victor 'Vic' Vance (Dorian Missick) who's kicked out of the army and precedes to rise through the ranks of multiple gangs in the glamourous and dangerous world of Vice City in 1984.

In 1974, Snake (a.k.a. Big Boss) is no longer part of the US special forces and has his own merc team. While on a mission in South America, they encounter a strange hostile merc unit with far superior equipment than their latest tech.

Ten years before Sora held the Keyblade, three young Keyblade wielders bound by friendship, face being torn apart by the sinister monsters terrorizing other worlds and the manipulative mastermind behind them.

Follows Daxter on how he became a hero and freed Jak at the beginning of Jak II (2003).

Triad gangster Huang Lee arrives in Liberty City to return a family heirloom and seek vengeance upon the thugs who murdered his father.

LocoRoco is a platform video game developed by SCE Japan Studio and published by Sony Computer Entertainment, which was released for the PlayStation Portable handheld game console.

The Helghast returned, and stronger than ever under the brutal leadership of General Armin Metrac. As the fate of the planet hangs in the balance, one soldier is sent on an impossible mission - Metrac must be defeated.

In an earlier time, when still in service to the gods, Kratos must fight to save the land from a growing darkness.

A re-release containing both Castlevania: Rondo of Blood and Castlevania: Symphony of the Night.

Patapon is a video game published originally for the PlayStation Portable handheld game console combining game play features of a rhythm game and a god game.

James Grayson, a marine deserts the army to destroy chimera conversion centers to avenge his brother, because of this, he is sentenced to death for desertion. James is pardoned by the French resistance to destroy more conversion centers.
